===Adjective===
{{en-adj|head=[[in]] [[control]]}}

# {{context|idiomatic}} When one is [[controlling]] a machine, or a situation, or an activity. Similar to [[in charge]], but one person can be officially in charge, while another person is, in fact, in control.
#: ''The General said that his troops were now '''in control''' of the situation.''

